10px;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Programming note:</strong><em> Money S=
tuff will be off tomorrow and Monday, back on Tuesday.</em></p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">TMTG / DWAC</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Digital World Acquisition Corp. is a special-p=
urpose acquisition company that has <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlua=
W9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTAtMjEvbWF0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1kb25hbGQt=
dHJ1bXAtZG9lcy1hLXNwYWM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDkwMTIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1=
lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwOTAxJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj=
1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBec638d81" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" it=
emscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  signed a deal</=
a> to merge with Trump Media &amp; Technology Group Corp., which runs Donal=
d Trump=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9CTruth Social=E2=80=9D network,=C2=A0and take it =
public.=C2=A0Like most SPACs, DWAC has a time limit to complete its deal: I=
ts corporate charter says that, if it has not completed a merger by Sept. 8=
 =E2=80=94=C2=A0next Thursday =E2=80=94=C2=A0it has to close up shop and re=
turn its money to shareholders. It is definitely not going to complete its=
=C2=A0merger with TMTG=C2=A0by next Thursday. (The main holdup is that the =
US Securities and Exchange Commission needs to review and sign off on the <=
a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR=
0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE4NDk2MzUvMDAwMTE5MzEyNT=
IyMTUwODAxL2QyMjYyMDVkczQuaHRt/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd785f7d5" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 proxy statement</a> for that merger; the SEC has <a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cueWFob28uY29=
tL3ZpZGVvL3NlYy1leHBhbmRzLWludmVzdGlnYXRpb24tZG9uYWxkLXRydW1wLTE0MzE1Njg1OC=
5odG1s/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfe4461cf" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> various questions</a>.)=
 Actually DWAC can <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE4ND=
k2MzUvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIxMTEzNTQxL3RtMjEyNzAzNWQxXzQyNGI0Lmh0bQ/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cBf9ced843" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> extend that deadline by six months</a>, if i=
ts sponsors put up some more money, but six months probably isn=E2=80=99t e=
nough either.=C2=A0So DWAC has <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci=
9kYXRhLzE4NDk2MzUvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMjI5NjYzL2QzODY5MDZkZGVmMTRhLmh0bQ/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cBd717203f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> asked its shareholders for a longer e=
xtension</a>: It has asked them to vote to approve an amendment to its char=
ter to extend the deadline by a year to Sept. 8, 2023.<a class=3D"footnote-=
index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; di=
splay: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a> The vote will be held at an online special meeting of shareholders nex=
t Tuesday, Sept. 6, two days before the current deadline.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you are a DWAC shareholder, how should you =
vote on this proposal? There is really only one conceivable answer. Whether=
 or not you like Donald Trump, TMTG, Truth Social, etc.,<a class=3D"footnot=
e-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; =
display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0the simple fact is that DWAC=E2=80=99s stock closed yesterday at =
$24.38. When DWAC went public, it sold stock for $10 per share, and it has =
about $10.20 per share =E2=80=94=C2=A0about $293 million total =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0in its trust right now. If it shuts down and returns money to shareholde=
rs, you=E2=80=99ll get $10.20. If it hangs around for another year trying t=
o close its deal with TMTG, well, I don=E2=80=99t know what will happen. Ma=
ybe it will never close the deal and end up paying shareholders back their =
$10.20 a year from now. Maybe it will close the deal and TMTG will be a dis=
aster and the shares will end up being worth $5, or $0. Maybe it will close=
 the deal and TMTG will be a spectacular success and the shares will end up=
 being worth $1,000. But the point is that, if DWAC gets this extension and=
 can hang around for another year trying to close the deal, you=E2=80=99ll =
be able to sell your DWAC stock on Sept. 9=C2=A0for $24 or so.<a class=3D"f=
ootnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !impor=
tant; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a> If it doesn=E2=80=99t, you=E2=80=99ll just get $10.20. The stock price=
 is much higher than the cash-out value, so you should vote to keep it goin=
g.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is not investing advice, but it is pretty=
 obvious, and I doubt anyone is going to vote no. Even if you hold DWAC sto=
ck for some reason and think =E2=80=9CTMTG is a puff of vapor, its real val=
ue is=C2=A0zero, I=E2=80=99d rather have the cash,=E2=80=9D who cares, you =
should sell the stock today for $24.38, which is more cash than $10.20.<a c=
lass=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" style=3D"color: #000000; text-=
decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color:=
 #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transpare=
nt !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a>=C2=A0Presumably the=C2=A0<em>buyer=C2=A0</em>would think the real valu=
e of TMTG is at least $24.38. So everyone who owns DWAC stock at $24.38 sho=
uld vote yes on the extension, and nobody who owns DWAC stock is likely to =
vote no.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is, however, a third option, which is no=
t to vote at all. And not voting is equivalent to <a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9=
BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE4NDk2MzUvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMjI5NjYzL2QzODY5MDZkZG=
VmMTRhLmh0bQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCd717203f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" item=
scope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> voting against the=
 extension</a>: =E2=80=9CThe affirmative vote of at least 65% of the Compan=
y=E2=80=99s outstanding shares of common stock =E2=80=A6 will be required t=
o approve the Extension Amendment Proposal.=E2=80=9D About 17.9% of those s=
hares are owned by DWAC=E2=80=99s sponsor and friends, who will presumably =
vote yes, but you still need another 47.1% (or roughly 57% of the public sh=
areholders) to get to 65%. If DWAC can=E2=80=99t get a majority of its shar=
eholders to vote, it will have to cash them out, which they don=E2=80=99t w=
ant.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-5" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: t=
ransparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So, rationally, they should all vote, and vote=
 yes. But there is no guarantee in life that every single shareholder of th=
e SPAC that is going to buy Donald Trump=E2=80=99s social media company=C2=
=A0is entirely rational. DWAC is more or less a meme stock, with a largely =
retail investor base. And meme-stock retail investors, <a href=3D"https://l=
ink.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb2=
1iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDgtMjQvYW1jLXMtYXBlcy1taWdodC1zd=
Gljay1hcm91bmQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDkwMTIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1=
dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwOTAxJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN=
0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB108c8167" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  as we have discussed r=
ecently</a>, sometimes don=E2=80=99t vote. For instance the SPAC that took =
Lucid Group Inc. public had to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6Ly9tYXJrZXRzLmJ1c2luZXNzaW5zaWRlci5jb2=
0vbmV3cy9zdG9ja3Mvd2hhdC1zLWdvaW5nLW9uLXdpdGgtbHVjaWQtc3BhYy1wYXJ0bmVyLWNod=
XJjaGlsbC1jYXBpdGFsLXMtc3RvY2stMTAzMDYzODI1MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5e59=
0c1e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" styl=
e=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width:=
 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-=
color: #ccc;"> adjourn its shareholder vote</a> on that deal because it had=
 a lot of retail shareholders and struggled to get them to vote, even thoug=
h the stock was trading in the $20s at the time and shareholders clearly lo=
ved the deal. (Eventually they=C2=A0approved it.) And that was a merger vot=
e; this is a boring extension-of-deadline vote, where it might be harder to=
 get enthusiasm.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I have no idea if DWAC will have any trouble g=
etting its vote, but I will say that its public filings about the vote are =
a little sweaty. Here=E2=80=99s one <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZ=
Gdhci9kYXRhLzE4NDk2MzUvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMjM1Njk1L2Q1MjUyOTdkZGVmYTE0YS5odG0/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe3755e13" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">from this morning</a>, telling s=
hareholders that they should have gotten an email with voting instructions =
and adding, in all caps, =E2=80=9CPLEASE REMEMBER TO CHECK YOUR SPAM FOLDER=
 FOR THE EMAIL.=E2=80=9D And=C2=A0here=E2=80=99s=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmd=
