<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">One touch</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In October 2017, Neil Phillips, the founder of=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28920355.270556/a=
HR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDktMDEvaGVkZ2Ut=
ZnVuZC1jby1mb3VuZGVyLXBoaWxsaXBzLWNoYXJnZWQtd2l0aC1tYXJrZXQtbWFuaXB1bGF0aW9=
uP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA5MDEyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT=
1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDkwMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cB2ea899b7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  macro hedge fund Glen Point Capital<=
/a>, made a macro bet on the South African rand (generally referred to as Z=
AR). The rand was trading at about 14 to the US dollar, and Phillips though=
t it would go up. (That is, the dollar would fall against the rand: A lower=
 number means a stronger rand.) He made a high-leverage, risky bet on that =
thesis: He went to a bank and bought a one-touch barrier option, just a sim=
ple binary bet that would pay his fund $20 million if the US dollar bought =
fewer than 12.5 rand at any point =E2=80=94=C2=A0even for a second =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0between Oct. 30, 2017 and Jan. 2, 2018, and zero if it did not. I =
don=E2=80=99t know how much he paid for this option, though casually using =
a Bloomberg model with historical data suggests it was worth maybe about $2=
 million. You get 10 times your money if the rand strengthens dramatically;=
 you lose your bet if it doesn=E2=80=99t.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He was right! On Dec. 17, Cyril Ramaphosa was =
elected as the new leader of South Africa=E2=80=99s ruling African National=
 Congress party, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2=
8920355.270556/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAxNy8xMi8xOC93b3JsZC9hZnJp=
Y2EvcmFtYXBob3NhLWFuYy1zb3V0aC1hZnJpY2EuaHRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB706=
fbfc8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;"> which was seen as</a> =E2=80=9Ca victory for reformers in t=
he A.N.C., which wants to root out corruption and woo back foreign investor=
s.=E2=80=9D And foreign investors were wooed: The rand traded at about 13.6=
 to the dollar a week before Ramaphosa=E2=80=99s election; it was at about =
12.6=C2=A0a week after.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Unfortunately Phillips needed a slightly lower=
 number. If the rand traded to 12.499, he made $20 million. If it stayed at=
=C2=A012.501 or higher, he got zero. So here=E2=80=99s a case that <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuanVzdGljZS5nb3YvdXNhby1zZG55L3ByL2NvLWZvdW5kZXItYW5kLWNoaWVmLWludmVz=
dG1lbnQtb2ZmaWNlci1sb25kb24tYmFzZWQtaGVkZ2UtZnVuZC1jaGFyZ2VkLWZ4LW1hcmtldA/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0989002a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> US federal prosecutors filed ag=
ainst Phillips today</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">With the $20 Million One Touch Option set to e=
xpire in a matter of days without having been triggered, on December 26, 20=
17 (Boxing Day), PHILLIPS engaged in a scheme to intentionally and artifici=
ally manipulate the USD/ZAR rate to drive the rate below 12.50 and trigger =
payment under the $20 Million One Touch Option. PHILLIPS caused and sought =
to cause the USD/ZAR exchange rate to fall below 12.50 by engaging in FX sp=
ot trades in which he caused hundreds of millions of USD to be exchanged fo=
r ZAR. PHILLIPS engaged in this USD/ZAR FX spot trading for the express pur=
pose of artificially driving the USD/ZAR rate below 12.50. On December 26, =
2017, in the hours that followed the completion of the USD/ZAR FX spot trad=
ing directed by PHILLIPS, the USD/ZAR rate once again increased and returne=
d to levels above the 12.50 barrier and did not go below that rate for the =
remainder of the day.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In particular, during the span of less than an=
 hour between shortly before midnight London time on December 25, 2017 (Chr=
istmas Day), and approximately 12:45 a.m. London time on December 26, 2017 =
(Boxing Day), PHILLIPS personally directed a Singapore-based employee (=E2=
=80=9CCC-1=E2=80=9D) of a bank (=E2=80=9CBank-3=E2=80=9D) to sell, on behal=
f of Hedge Fund-1, a total of approximately $725 million USD in exchange fo=
r approximately 9,070,902,750 ZAR.=C2=A0During the course of that approxima=
tely one-hour period, PHILLIPS, through his trading, caused the USD/ZAR rat=
e to fall substantially until the rate went just below 12.50. As soon as PH=
ILLIPS had achieved his objective and the USD/ZAR rate fell below 12.50 due=
 to PHILLIPS=E2=80=99 manipulative spot trading activity, PHILLIPS immediat=
ely directed that CC-1 cease trading. PHILLIPS provided trading instruction=
s to CC-1 through Bloomberg chat messages while PHILLIPS was located in Sou=
th Africa and while CC-1 was located in Singapore. In these Bloomberg chat =
messages, PHILLIPS explicitly directed CC-1 to continue selling until the U=
SD/ZAR rate fell below 12.50 and PHILLIPS expressly stated that PHILLIPS=E2=
=80=99 purpose in directing these trades was to drive the USD/ZAR rate belo=
w 12.50 stating, among other things, =E2=80=9Cmy aim is to trade thru 50,=
=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9C[n]eed it to trade thru 50. 4990 is fine,=E2=80=9D and =
=E2=80=9C[g]et it thru.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0Once PHILLIPS was informed by CC-1 th=
at the USD/ZAR had traded at below 12.50, PHILLIPS immediately instructed C=
C-1 to =E2=80=9Cstop=E2=80=9D trading and asked for proof =E2=80=9Cof the p=
rint.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you sell USD 725 million for ZAR 9,070,902,=
750, you are getting an average price of ZAR 12.51 per dollar. But your=C2=
=A0<em>last=C2=A0</em>trade is at, in this case, 12.4975, and that=E2=80=99=
s all you need to get paid $20 million. Then I suppose you can exchange you=
r ZAR for dollars again. You=E2=80=99ll have some slippage. But even if you=
 pay ZAR=C2=A012.75 per dollar on the way back =E2=80=94=C2=A0almost 2% hig=
her than you got on the way in =E2=80=94=C2=A0the trade will cost you about=
 $13.5 million, which is still less than $20 million. Trading hundreds of m=
illions of dollars for ZAR very inefficiently is still worth doing, if you =
have a $20 million one-touch option that expires in a week. Except obviousl=
y for the threat of criminal prosecution.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The way I think about market manipulation is t=
hat there are three main elements:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You are buying or selling a lot of so=
mething, with the effect of moving its price.=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"mar=
gin-bottom: 5px;">You are making money on a side trade. Buying a lot of ZAR=
, moving the price up, and then selling it is not generally a good way to d=
o market manipulation, because it will come back down as you sell it; you w=
ill end up losing money on transaction costs. (This is why the federal case=
 against Bill Hwang for allegedly manipulating a bunch of stocks <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMjcvYmlsbC1od2FuZy1=
hcnJlc3QtaW5zaWRlLXRoZS12aWNpb3VzLWN5Y2xlLW9mLWFyY2hlZ29zLWNvbGxhcHNlP2NtcG=
lkPUJCRDA5MDEyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzb=
GV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDkwMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8=
524a319a23cB5e5eb556" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">  is so weird</a>: They went up when he bough=
t them and down when he sold them, and he <em>lost=C2=A0</em>tons of money.=
) But buying a lot of ZAR, moving the price up, selling it, and=C2=A0<em>ma=
king $20 million on a derivatives trade</em>, sure, fine, that looks like m=
arket manipulation.=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You are =
sending people messages that say =E2=80=9Clol I am manipulating this market=
!=E2=80=9D Buying a lot of something can=E2=80=99t be illegal on its own: M=
aybe you like the thing. But buying a lot of it and=C2=A0<em>saying=C2=A0</=
em>that you are doing it to move the price suggests bad intent.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is some of that here. From <a href=3D"ht=
tps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3c=
uanVzdGljZS5nb3YvdXNhby1zZG55L3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvZmlsZS8xNTMwMjE2L2Rvd25sb2=
Fk/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe34d3c84" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the indictment</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the Bloomberg chat messages between NEIL PH=
ILLIPS, the defendant, and CC-1, PHILLIPS explicitly directed CC-1 to conti=
nue selling until the USD/ZAR rate fell below 12.50 and expressly stated th=
at PHILLIPS=E2=80=99 purpose in directing these USD/ZAR spot trades was to =
drive the USD/ZAR rate below 12.50. For example:</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At approximately 12:09 a.m. London time on Dec=
ember 26, 2017, PHILLIPS stated, in substance and in part, =E2=80=9Cmy aim =
is to trade thru 50.=E2=80=9D CC-1 responded =E2=80=9COk sure.=E2=80=9D =E2=
=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At approximately 12:25 a.m. London time on Dec=
ember 26, 2017, PHILLIPS again stated, in substance and in part, =E2=80=9CN=
eed it to trade thru 50. 4990 is fine.=E2=80=9D ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At approximately 12:44 a.m. London time on Dec=
ember 26, 2017, C-1 told PHILLIPS, in substance and in part, =E2=80=9Cwe ju=
st sold at 4990.=E2=80=9D Approximately one minute later CC-1 stated, in su=
bstance and in part, =E2=80=9CWe are finishing now, will be 725 mio [millio=
n USD] all day.=E2=80=9D PHILLIPS responded, in substance and in part at ap=
proximately 12:45 a.m. London time, =E2=80=9CPls. [please] get me prof [pro=
of] of the print and stip [sic] stop,=E2=80=9D referring to the fact that C=
C-1 should cease trading immediately.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another, optional but helpful, element of mark=
et manipulation is trading at an illiquid time so that your trades can have=
 the most impact. If you are trading a lot of volume at midnight on Christm=
as, that does look kind of weird.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway the indictment quotes an investor lette=
r that Phillips sent in January, bragging about his macro call =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0=E2=80=9CWe had anticipated the potential for large swings in South Afri=
can assets around the ANC electoral conference=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0but =
not disclosing the alleged manipulation. It would be funny if his investor =
letter <em>did=C2=A0</em>brag about market manipulation.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The indictment also says that =E2=80=9COn or a=
bout December 26, 2017, in the hours that followed the completion of the ab=
ove-described USD/ZAR FX spot trading =E2=80=A6=C2=A0the USD/ZAR exchange r=
ate once again increased and returned to levels above the 12.50 barrier rat=
e and did not go below the rate of 12.50 for the remainder of the day.=E2=
=80=9D But Bloomberg data shows it trading at 12.2684 the next day, Dec. 27=
, and in fact trading below 12.50 for the next few months. Even without the=
 alleged manipulation, the barrier option would have paid off! The story in=
 this complaint seems to be that he made the right macro call, the market t=
raded in his direction, but it hadn=E2=80=99t=C2=A0<em>quite=C2=A0</em>gott=
en there and time was running out. So he allegedly got nervous and hurried =
it along, unnecessarily, as it turns out.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">People assume=C2=A0that stuff like this happen=
s all the time. There are round numbers in financial markets, and it is wid=
ely assumed that there are automatic trades that are triggered at those rou=
nd numbers. Some big fund has a stop-loss order saying that if this stock t=
rades below $100, they will sell the stock. Some hedge fund has a margin lo=
an against that stock and will get liquidated it if falls below $50. Some b=
ig bank has written some barrier options saying that if this currency trade=
s above 12.50, it will pay $20 million. Etc. If a price gets close to the r=
ound number, somebody can make a lot of money by trading a bit more of it, =
pushing the price=C2=A0<em>across=C2=A0</em>the round number and triggering=
 the stop orders or barrier options or margin calls or other automatic trad=
es.=C2=A0And so a certain amount of market lore, technical analysis, conspi=
racy theories or just general explanations for daily price action are based=
 on this sort of theory, the idea that someone was targeting some specific =
level in order to trigger a profit. But you don=E2=80=99t see a ton of actu=
al cases brought. You=E2=80=99re not supposed to put it in writing!</p>
<table class=3D"liveintent-flex-ad" border=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspac=
ing=3D"0" align=3D"center">
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"2">
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28920355.270556/aH=
