<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcG=
luaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDgtMjIvbWVtZS1zdG9jay12YWNhdGlvbi1pcy1vdmVyP2Ntc=
GlkPUJCRDA5MDEyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdz=
bGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDkwMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b=
8524a319a23cBd7085269" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targe=
t=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bor=
der-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: s=
olid; background-color: #ccc;">  various substantive theories</a> of enviro=
nmental, social and governance investing, theories of what it is supposed t=
o do. Some of those theories are about maximizing financial returns, while =
others are about achieving environmental, social and governance goals with =
your investment dollars.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But there is also just a=C2=A0<em>marketing=C2=
=A0</em>theory of ESG, which is that investors want ESG investments (for so=
me substantive reason or combination of reasons) and are willing to pay hig=
her fees for them. So if you are a big institutional investment manager, yo=
u should slap an =E2=80=9CESG=E2=80=9D name on your regular old investment =
funds, to attract more clients and charge them more. This seems to be a big=
 business, to the point that regulators and investors <a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21=
iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDUtMjMvdGhlLXNlYy1nb2VzLWFmdGVyLW=
dyZWVud2FzaGluZz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwOTAxMjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJ=
nV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjA5MDEmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5=
c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf68ee8ee" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  complain=C2=A0a lot ab=
out =E2=80=9Cgreenwashing,=E2=80=9D</a> where an investment manager pretend=
s=C2=A0that a regular fund is an ESG fund for marketing reasons.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But that feels like a three-months-ago sort of=
 issue, and these days =E2=80=9CESG=E2=80=9D has become a marketing=C2=A0<e=
m>problem</em>. The US Republican Party has decided that ESG is bad, and is=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28920355.270556/a=
HR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDgtMzEvZ29wLXMt=
d2FyLW9uLWVzZy13aWxsLWhhdmUtbG9zc2VzLW9uLWJvdGgtc2lkZXM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDkwMTI=
yX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3=
Rlcm09MjIwOTAxJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBca6=
55046" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;">  pushing public pension</a> funds in Republican-controlled =
states to avoid ESG funds. This is tricky for big institutional fund manage=
rs, because =E2=80=9CESG=E2=80=9D is probably still=C2=A0<em>good </em>mark=
eting too. If you call your fund =E2=80=9CESG,=E2=80=9D that will make some=
 people more likely to buy it and other people less likely to buy it, and i=
f you are a giant institutional investor like BlackRock Inc. you will do a =
lot of vague balancing to try to appeal to everyone.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But this is also a huge marketing opportunity =
for=C2=A0<em>other</em>, smaller<em>=C2=A0</em>investment managers to try t=
o capture anti-ESG market share from BlackRock by leaning into being=C2=A0N=
ot ESG. Like if you just run a regular mutual fund, the incentive six month=
s ago was to rebrand it as an ESG fund and say =E2=80=9Cooh, we think about=
 climate change, whatever=E2=80=9D to capture ESG dollars. Now, if you run =
a regular mutual fund, there is an incentive to rebrand it as an anti-ESG f=
und and say =E2=80=9Cwe absolutely never think about climate change at all=
=E2=80=9D to capture state pension money from Republican-controlled states.=
 Or start a new fund company, why not.=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvb=
S9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDktMDEvd29rZS1pbmMtYXV0aG9yLXMtZmlybS10YXJnZXRz=
LWJsYWNrcm9jay1lc2ctaW52ZXN0aW5nP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA5MDEyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9=
tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDkwMSZ1dG1fY2=
FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB88fa1113" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">So</a>:=
</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Enter [Vivek] Ramaswamy, 37, author of the 202=
1 book <em>Woke, Inc.: Inside Corporate America=E2=80=99s Social Justice Sc=
am</em>. Sensing opportunity, he=E2=80=99s started his own investment compa=
ny with backing from billionaire investors Peter Thiel and Bill Ackman.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ramaswamy=E2=80=99s little company, Strive Ass=
et Management LLC, has crazy big ambitions. =E2=80=A6 Ramaswamy insists Str=
ive will one day take on BlackRock, a leading proponent of sustainable inve=
sting. New York-based BlackRock manages $8.5 trillion. Strive, located near=
 Columbus, Ohio, manages one fund, DRLL, worth about $300 million. The firm=
 has filed to start several more funds. BlackRock declined to comment. =E2=
=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ramaswamy, too, says his message is nonpartisa=
n and expresses disappointment that it =E2=80=9Chas been too limited to the=
 American right. It=E2=80=99s not for lack of effort.=E2=80=9D Yet his pitc=
h sounds a lot like a political manifesto. In language reminiscent of a Don=
ald Trump rally or Fox pundit Tucker Carlson (Ramaswamy has appeared on Car=
lson=E2=80=99s show), he says Strive will speak for the =E2=80=9Cforgotten,=
=E2=80=9D the =E2=80=9Cdisempowered,=E2=80=9D the =E2=80=9Cabused=E2=80=9D=
=E2=80=94for the 100 million-plus ordinary investors whose voices are being=
 drowned out by elitist big money.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A Zelig of the conference circuit, he=E2=80=99=
s cultivating the red-state governors, treasurers, and pension officials wh=
o decide where the public=E2=80=99s money flows. =E2=80=9CMoney doesn=E2=80=
=99t talk, it screams,=E2=80=9D Ramaswamy says. =E2=80=9CWe allow people to=
 speak in a way that they haven=E2=80=99t been able to speak before.=E2=80=
=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You can, and I=E2=80=99m sure=C2=A0Ramaswamy d=
oes, have substantive theories=C2=A0of anti-ESG. Just as with ESG, these th=
eories might be about maximizing financial returns (=E2=80=9CESG trades ret=
urns for wokeness, and I will focus only on returns=E2=80=9D) or about achi=
eving political or other goals (=E2=80=9CESG hurts coal miners and I want t=
o help them=E2=80=9D). But there is also just an obvious marketing theory o=
f anti-ESG, which is that a bunch of huge public pensions are looking for a=
nti-ESG places to put their money, and if you can meet that demand then tha=
t=E2=80=99s a good business.</p>
