<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">My understanding is that geolocation data is v=
aluable. If you can track where millions of people are every day, you can t=
urn that knowledge into money, by serving them relevant ads or whatever. Th=
is implies that knowing where=C2=A0<em>one=C2=A0</em>person is every day is=
 valuable, though not necessarily=C2=A0<em>very=C2=A0</em>valuable; there a=
re only so many ads you can serve that one person. But if that person is a =
billionaire then, sure, you=E2=80=99ve got something there. There are monet=
ization opportunities.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And there does seem to be a weird niche busine=
ss model of,=C2=A0like, Knowing Where a Billionaire Is Every Day. We <a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDgtMjkvbXVzay10cml=
lcy1hLW5ldy13YXktb3V0LW9mLXR3aXR0ZXI_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDkwMTIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdX=
RtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwOTAxJnV0b=
V9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB44100978" itemprop=3D"=
StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  ta=
lked the other day</a> about the college student who is in the business of =
tracking Elon Musk=E2=80=99s private jet; he does not seem to have figured =
out monetization yet, but he=E2=80=99s got some promising ideas.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or what if you knew where Bitcoin evangelist a=
nd former MicroStrategy Inc. Chief Executive Officer Michael Saylor was eve=
ry day for the last 10 years? By following him around every day, or by trac=
king his social-media posts to put him in locations, or some other method? =
Could you monetize that? I bet you could think of ideas. Maybe there are cr=
ypto startup founders who would love to coincidentally run into him on his =
way to work, and who would pay you a bit of money to improve their odds. Ma=
ybe you could use this data somehow to predict the price of MicroStrategy s=
tock, or of Bitcoin.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But if you=E2=80=99re a=C2=A0<em>tax=C2=A0</em=
>expert, you might notice another, more surprising monetization angle. If y=
ou followed Michael Saylor around =E2=80=94=C2=A0on Facebook or in real lif=
e =E2=80=94=C2=A0you might notice that he spends a lot of time in his Washi=
ngton, D.C., apartment, or in his=C2=A0<em>other </em>Washington, D.C., apa=
rtment, or on his yacht docked in Georgetown, or on his=C2=A0<em>other=C2=
=A0</em>yacht docked in Georgetown. Specifically, you might notice that he =
spends more than 183 days a year in his Washington, D.C., yachts and apartm=
ents.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is a magic number because someone who=C2=
=A0lives in Washington, D.C., for at least 183 days a year is legally=C2=A0=
a Washington, D.C., resident and has to pay District=C2=A0income taxes. Say=
lor, apparently, does not: He claims to be a resident of Florida, which <a =
href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0c=
HM6Ly90YXhmb3VuZGF0aW9uLm9yZy9zdGF0ZS9mbG9yaWRh/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1d=
76ca52" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;"> does not have</a> an individual income tax. You could turn=
 him in to the Washington, D.C., authorities for not paying taxes, and then=
, under District law, you can get a cut of the taxes that he owes. (The cut=
 is roughly 25%, though with various penalties, triple damages, etc., you m=
ight end up getting much more.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote=
-6" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !impo=
rtant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[6]</span>
</a>) Saylor makes a lot of money, which means that he might owe a lot of t=
axes, which means that you can get a lot of money for this business.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGlj=
bGVzLzIwMjItMDgtMzEvbWljcm9zdHJhdGVneS1zLXNheWxvci1zdWVkLWJ5LWRjLWZvci1pbmN=
vbWUtdGF4LWF2b2lkYW5jZT9jbXBpZD1CQkQwOTAxMjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPW=
VtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjA5MDEmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduP=
W1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa49dbc07" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" it=
emscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Anyway</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Washington, D.C., is suing MicroStrategy Inc. =
co-founder and Executive Chairman Michael Saylor -- probably best known as =
the largest corporate buyer of Bitcoin -- for tax fraud, claiming that he s=
kipped out on paying more than $25 million in income taxes despite living i=
n the district for more than a decade.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">According to the lawsuit, which was filed with=
 the D.C. Superior Court=E2=80=99s civil division, Saylor knowingly avoided=
 paying taxes he owed since 2005 by fraudulently claiming to be a resident =
of other, lower-taxes jurisdictions, including Virginia and Florida. It cla=
ims that Saylor lived in a luxury penthouse on the Georgetown waterfront an=
d docked multiple yachts on the district=E2=80=99s Potomac riverfront. =E2=
=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI respectfully disagree with the posi=
tion of the District of Columbia, and look forward to a fair resolution in =
the courts,=E2=80=9D Saylor said in a statement provided to Bloomberg News.=
 He said he moved to Miami Beach from Virginia a decade ago after purchasin=
g a historic house there. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The district=E2=80=99s case originated with a =
whistleblower, who filed a complaint under seal in April 2021 under D.C.=E2=
=80=99s False Claims Act.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CDemonstrating his disdain for the rul=
es that everyone else has to live by, Saylor publicly flaunted his billiona=
ire lifestyle while bragging to his friends and associates about how he was=
 evading District taxes,=E2=80=9D according to the whistleblower complaint.=
=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6Ly9vYWcuZGMuZ292L3NpdGVzL2RlZmF1=
bHQvZmlsZXMvMjAyMi0wOC9UcmlidXR1bSUyMHYuJTIwU2F5bG9yJTIwLSUyMERDJTIwRkNBJTI=
wQ29tcGxhaW50XzAucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe000aa24" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the whist=
le-blower complaint</a>, which says that the whistle-blower is an entity ca=
lled=C2=A0Tributum LLC. A sample:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For some individuals, it would be =
difficult to reconstruct their past day-to-day locations and establish that=
 they spent the majority of their time in the District. Saylor, on the othe=
r hand, left a trail of information to reconstruct his movements to and fro=
m the District. This trail includes, among other things: location-specific =
social media posts; local newspaper articles chronicling parties he hosted =
in the District; witness accounts from Saylor=E2=80=99s inner circle; and F=
ederal Aviation Administration (=E2=80=9CFAA=E2=80=9D) flight information f=
or his company=E2=80=99s private jet, each showing exactly when he left the=
 District and when he returned. Thus Saylor=E2=80=99s scheme was exposed fo=
r the world, and this Court, to see.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6Ly9vYWcuZGMuZ292L3NpdGVzL2Rl=
ZmF1bHQvZmlsZXMvMjAyMi0wOC8yMDIyLTA4LTIyJTIwQ29tcGxhaW50JTIwaW4lMjBJbnRlcnZ=
lbnRpb25fMC5wZGY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf1d9cb77" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" =
itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-dec=
oration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0=
00000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the D.C. attor=
ney general=E2=80=99s complaint</a>, which includes citations to those soci=
al media posts:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On September 9, 2012, Defendant Sa=
ylor posted to his Facebook account a photograph of his residence at 3030 K=
 Street NW, apparently taken from the Potomac while aboard one of his yacht=
s. The post pinned Saylor=E2=80=99s location in =E2=80=9CWashington, D.C.=
=E2=80=9D and tagged James Augustus Seymour Van Wynen, the architect overse=
eing the penthouse renovations. The caption read, =E2=80=9CGazing wistfully=
 at my future home while I wait for James to crack the whip on the contract=
ors and herd the cats. I wonder if Tony Stark would be so patient=E2=80=A6.=
=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Don=E2=80=99t say that it=E2=80=99s your =E2=
=80=9Cfuture home=E2=80=9D if you do not intend to be domiciled there for t=
ax reasons, is I guess the conclusion here. Also, though, there are a lot o=
f people who make a lot of money and who have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/28920355.270556/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmN=
vbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDYtMTAvd2FsbC1zdHJlZXQtbW92ZXMtc291dGgtZ29sZG=
1hbi1ibGFja3N0b25lLWNyb3dkLWZsb3JpZGEtZWxpdGUtcHJpdmF0ZS1zY2hvb2xzP2NtcGlkP=
UJCRDA5MDEyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0=
dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDkwMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524=
a319a23cB2c2bd20f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D=
"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;">  moved to Florida</a> for tax reasons in recent=
 years. If you tracked 100 of them, is it possible that you=E2=80=99d find =
one or two who actually spend 183 days a year in New York or California or =
some other higher-tax jurisdiction? Is this a business model that can scale=
 up=C2=A0beyond Saylor?</p>
